createHyperEdge

public HyperEdge createHyperEdge(cytoscape.CyNode node1,
                                 java.lang.String edgeIType1,
                                 cytoscape.CyNode node2,
                                 java.lang.String edgeIType2,
                                 cytoscape.CyNetwork net)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdgeFactory
Create and return a HyperEdge connecting two CyNodes. The HyperEdge will contain a newly created ConnectorNode. Two CyEdges will be created that connect each CyNode to this Connector CyNode. The edge interaction types specify the type attribute to associate with each CyEdge created and whether each node is the source or target of each CyEdge.

Specified by:
createHyperEdge in interface HyperEdgeFactory
Parameters:
node1 - the first node to add to the HyperEdge.
edgeIType1 - the edge interaction type of node1. edgeIType1 also determines the Role played by node1 within the newly created CyEdge. For details, see the discussion in this class description and the example in EdgeTypeMap.
node2 - the second node to add to the HyperEdge.
edgeIType2 - the edge interaction type of node2. edgeIType2 also determines the Role played by node2 within the newly created CyEdge. For details, see the discussion in this class description and the example in EdgeTypeMap.
Returns:
the newly created HyperEdge. After the HyperEdge is created, all HyperEdgeManager NewObjectListeners are notified by invoking their NewObjectListener.objectCreated() methods about the creation of this new HyperEdge.

createHyperEdge

public HyperEdge createHyperEdge(cytoscape.CyNode[] nodes,
                                 java.lang.String[] edgeITypes,
                                 cytoscape.CyNetwork net)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdgeFactory
Creates a HyperEdge based on a an array of CyNodes along with a corresponding array of Roles. The HyperEdge will contain a newly created ConnectorNode. CyEdges will be created what connect each given CyNode to this ConnectorNode.

Specified by:
createHyperEdge in interface HyperEdgeFactory
Parameters:
nodes - an Array of CyNodes to be members of this HyperEdge.
edgeITypes - an Array of corresponding edge interaction types (one for each CyNode) used for setting the type attribute of the CyEdges created and the role played by each node in each created CyEdge. For details, see the discussion in this class description and the example in EdgeTypeMap.
Returns:
the newly created HyperEdge. After the HyperEdge is created, all HyperEdgeManager NewObjectListeners are notified by invoking their NewObjectListener.objectCreated() methods about the creation of this new HyperEdge.

Description copied from interface: HyperEdgeFactory
Creates a HyperEdge based on a List of CyNodes along with a corresponding List of CyEdge interaction types. The HyperEdge will contain a newly created ConnectorNode. For each CyNode given, an CyEdge will be created that connects this CyNode to the ConnectorNode.

Returns:
the newly created HyperEdge. After the HyperEdge is created, all HyperEdgeManager NewObjectListeners are notified by invoking their NewObjectListener.objectCreated() methods about the creation of this new HyperEdge.

createHyperEdge

public HyperEdge createHyperEdge(java.util.Map<cytoscape.CyNode,java.lang.String> node_edgeIType_map,
                                 cytoscape.CyNetwork net)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdgeFactory
Creates a HyperEdge based on a map of a CyNode key to an CyEdge interaction type value. Each key and value must be non-null and all values must be a non-empty edge interaction types. The HyperEdge will contain a newly created ConnectorNode. For each edge interaction type value associated with a CyNode key, an CyEdge will be created that connects the CyNode key to the HyperEdge CyNode. The type attribute of this CyEdge will be the edge interaction type value and specify whether the node is the source or target of this CyEdge. For details on how each edge interaction type value determines the corresponding node's role within each new CyEdge, see the discussion in this class description and the example in EdgeTypeMap.

Specified by:
createHyperEdge in interface HyperEdgeFactory
Returns:
the newly created HyperEdge. After the HyperEdge is created, all HyperEdgeManager NewObjectListeners are notified by invoking their NewObjectListener.objectCreated() methods about the creation of this new HyperEdge.
See Also:
HyperEdgeFactory, EdgeTypeMap
